Relief for the 2004 Indian Ocean tsunami victims continues.
More than $10 billion has been pledged by 42 countries and individuals.
Debt relief and loans are also being offered.
Concerts, telethons, and charity auctions are among the methods being used to solicit donations.
President Bush made a personal contribution of $10,000.
Bush recruited Former Presidents Clinton and Bush, his father, to lead fundraising efforts in the U.S. President Bush signed a law permitting U.S. taxpayers to deduct contributions to tsunami relief in January 2005 from their 2004 returns.
The Canadian government will match all private donations to approved aid agencies.
